==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|chekmat||lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|eschec mat|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|ar|en}}, from {{etyl|fa|en}} {{term|شاه مات|tr=šāh māt|lit=the king is stumped, or ambushed|lang=fa}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈt͡ʃɛkmeɪt/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-us-checkmate.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪt|lang=en}}

